message: Happy New Year!
Excited to serve as co-chair of the Armenian Congressional Caucus for the 115th Congress and look forward to continuing our work within the Central Valley Armenian-American community!
Honored to be sworn in to the 115th Congress and grateful for the opportunity to serve.
New water legislation for a new Congress. It's time to grow our communities, grow our food, and grow our families.   Learn more about my bill, H.R. 23, the GROW Act here: http://bit.ly/2j20dk6

Ensuring our veterans have access to proper medical care is a small, yet important, symbol of gratitude for their service, especially when their medical conditions are a result of active service.   Today, I am proud to introduce H.R. 299, the Blue Water Navy Vietnam Veterans Act in the House of Representatives to expand benefits to veterans who were exposed to Agent Orange during Vietnam.
Incredibly grateful for the brave men and women who risk their lives to keep us safe. Thank you to all those who serve our communities! #LawEnforcementAppreciationDay
As we begin a new year, please, take a moment to complete this quick survey. Your answers will help me focus on the issues that are most important to you and your family during the 115th Congress.

Excited to again serve on the House Appropriations Committee and the Agriculture, Military Construction and Veteran Affairs, as well as the Transportation, Housing, and Urban Development Subcommittees.
It's always an honor to preside over the House as Speaker pro tempore. Catch me on CSPAN!

Cynthia Pollard with Aera Energy, Senator Andy Vidak, and Assemblyman Vince Fong joined me for quite the photo-op at the Annual Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. Community Awards Breakfast this morning in Bakersfield!
‚Ä™It's inauguration week in DC! Regardless of political beliefs, witnessing the peaceful transition of power is incredible.‚Ä¨
Getting ready for inauguration with ABC30 Action News right outside the Capitol!
#Inauguration tickets waiting to be picked up by #CA21 constituents! In DC for the festivities? Be sure to tag your photos #CA21InDC!
The first F-35's arrived at NAS Lemoore today. Excited to have the next generation of stealth fighter right here in the Central Valley!
Enjoyed meeting with Kings Community Action Organization and discussing early childhood education in the Valley!
‚Ä™Tune in now as I join Kim Stephens and Kopi Sotiropulos on KMPH FOX 26 to discuss the important issues impacting the Central Valley.
Enjoyed discussing education, immigration, and water with AP Government students from Sanger High this afternoon!
My Valentine today and every day!

I enjoyed the opportunity to discuss the need for immigration reform and legislative solutions with a great group of constituents this morning in Fresno. Thank you to the Fresno Area Hispanic Foundation and FWD.us for organizing the event!
Next month, I will be hosting a Community Resource Fair in Bakersfield. The event will provide attendees with valuable information about no-cost programs and services available to our community!

Speaking with my constituents is one of the most important and enjoyable parts of my job and I am excited to announce an additional way for you and I to communicate with each other. This Monday, I will host a Hometown Huddle and have one-on-one meetings with my constituents! Learn more here: http://bit.ly/CA21Huddle
Thank you Kings United Way for taking time to meet with me yesterday. Kings County appreciates everything you do four our community!
Hearing from my constituents is the best part of my job. Watch my Fox News debut to learn more about my work representing you in Congress and the ways you and I can stay in touch.

Today, The White House responded to Congress and issued a Major Disaster Declaration for California counties impacted by recent winter storms. Ensuring those communities impacted have the resources they need to clean up, rebuild, and make infrastructure repairs is absolutely critical.
Great event in Bakersfield this morning! Thank you to Community Action Partnership of Kern for discussing the great programs available in our community!

The Central Valley leads the nation in agriculture production because of the hard work of our farmers, ranchers, and ag workers. Thank you to all those who grow, pick, and process our nation‚Äôs food! #AgDay2017

As one of the few Portuguese-Americans in Congress, I enjoyed meeting Portuguese Minister of Foreign Affairs, Augusto Santos Silva yesterday. The Minister, Representative Costa, and I, were able to discuss the importance of the relationship between the United States and Portugal.

I'm honored to receive the 2017 Health Champion Award from the Central Valley Health Network. The role community health centers play in our healthcare system cannot be overstated and we are incredibly fortunate to have the Central Valley Health Network and its members serving our communities.
Today, the U.S. Bureau of Reclamation announced 100% water allocation for CVP contractors. This is encouraging and further emphasizes the need to continue to invest in our water infrastructure.

Excited to take part in tonight's Agriculture and Labor Town Hall hosted by FOX26 in Fresno. Watch LIVE online or on KMPH in Fresno or KBAK in Bakersfield. Submit your questions using #YourVoiceYourFuture.
‚Ä™Wishing you and your family a happy and blessed Easter.

Students from my own alma mater St. Rose-McCarthy Catholic School of Hanford are visiting Washington, DC this week and stopped by for a tour of the Capitol! If you live in the 21st District and are planning a visit to our nation's Capital, let us know. We'd love to show you around!
Students from Mary Immaculate Queen school made the trek from Lemoore, California all the way to Washington, DC this week. Hope you enjoyed the Capitol tour!

‚Ä™Last week, I had the opportunity to tour Munger Farms in Kern County and learn more about their blueberry operations. Did you know California produces more than 53 million pounds of blueberries each year?!‚Ä¨

Check out all the 2017 #CA21 Congressional Art Competition Submissions online now and vote for your favorite! The "likes" on each photo will be tallied and the winning piece of art will hang in one of my Congressional offices!  In addition, all submissions will be on display this Friday at the Kings Art Center in Hanford from 6:00 PM to 8:00 PM.

Thank you to all those who stopped by to support our local high school artists at the 2017 Congressional Art Competition exhibit! "Fan Favorite" voting is open till Wednesday, be sure to cast your vote here: http://bit.ly/21CAArt

Grateful to have had the opportunity to thank Corporal Ethan A. Martinez for his service to our country during my trip to East Asia this past week. Cpl Martinez is from Hanford and stationed at Camp Kinser in Okinawa, Japan.
As we commemorate the 102nd Anniversary of the Armenian Genocide, let us remember those whose lives were lost or forever changed by these tragic events.

It was an honor to greet Central Valley veterans as they visited the Korean War Memorial in Washington, DC today with Central Valley Honor Flight. There is nothing more humbling than having the opportunity to personally thank our nation's veterans for their service to our country.

I am excited to announce the winners of the 2017 Congressional Art Competition! The Central Valley has some incredible artists!   ‚Ä¢ First Place: Brianna Ozuna; Hanford High School ‚Ä¢ Second Place: Diana Valle; Hanford West High School ‚Ä¢ Third Place: Ava Torres; South High School ‚Ä¢ Fan Favorite #1: Emma Andrade; Riverdale High School ‚Ä¢ Fan Favorite #2: Stefani Sanchez; Sanger High School
Thanks for all your hard work interning, John. We are so proud of you! Congrats on your graduation from the George Mason LIFE program!

Providing our veterans with quality care is a small, yet important symbol of our gratitude for their service. Today, I had the opportunity to sit down with the Director of the Fresno VA, Stephen Bauman to discuss ways we can ensure our veterans are getting the care they deserve.

Got to check out the Associated Builders and Contractors Central California Chapter facility in Bakersfield this week. I appreciate the career and technical training opportunities they provide for our community.

For years, the Central Valley has lacked access to quality health care. In the Valley, we know possession of an insurance card does not equate to health care services and medical treatment. Watch my KSEE24 News interview with Evan Onstot on how the American Health Care Act will strengthen our health care system.

This #PoliceWeek2017, communities across the nation remember the brave men and women who gave their lives protecting ours. I am proud to support our nation‚Äôs law enforcement officers today and every day.
Interested in learning more about services and resources available to veterans in our community? If so, I hope you will attend my Veteran's Resource Workshop next month!

As a parent, there is absolutely nothing more important to me than ensuring families have access to quality, affordable health insurance.  Read my op-ed in The Fresno Bee to learn more about the American Health Care Act and how the bill will improve health care for families in the Central Valley.
Enjoyed showing the Torres family from Hanford and the Wilkin family from Kingsburg around the Capitol today! Be sure to contact my office if you are planning a trip to DC this summer!

Who better than 100+ #FosterYouthVoices to advocate on child welfare issues? Excited to learn more about this important issue from Cindy Barrera, a foster youth from #Lemoore while I show her around our nation's Capitol today! #DCShadowDay
Exciting news ‚Üí Today, the House passed my legislation to protect Americans, especially children, veterans, and senior citizens from becoming victims of identity theft.
While we enjoy the holiday weekend with our friends and family, let us remember the brave men and women who have made the ultimate sacrifice for our great nation.
Remembering heroes, like William Ralph Shockley from Selma at today's Memorial Day Service at Washington Colony Cemetery. We are forever grateful to all those who paid the ultimate price.
73 years later, we honor those who fought on the beaches of Normandy during World War II.  Today, let us remember those who made the ultimate sacrifice. #DDay

Today, I introduced a bill with Congressman Denham to correct California‚Äôs  Medicaid reimbursement method. By correcting the flawed method, we can encourage medical professionals to set up their practices in the Valley and provide medical services to ALL patients.

My view from today‚Äôs House Committee on Appropriations - Republicans Subcommittee Hearing examining the FY2018 budget request for the U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) with Secretary Ben Carson. HUD programs are incredibly important to rural areas such as California‚Äôs Central Valley.
Got to meet up with Richland Junior High School students from Shafter in the Capitol before they head back to California later today!
Thank you to all those who attended my Veterans Resource Workshop this past Saturday in Kings County. More importantly, thank you for your service - it is an honor to serve you in Congress.
‚Ä™Praying for Congressman Steve Scalise and staff injured in this morning's tragic incident. Thankful for our brave Capitol Police officers.

My office is currently seeking a wounded warrior or medically retired veteran for a two-year paid fellowship in my Bakersfield or Hanford Congressional Office. To learn more about the program, including requirements and how to apply, please visit the House of Representatives Wounded Warrior Program webpage.

While Americans throughout the country have been adversely impacted by the failed policies of Obamacare, my constituents have been especially harmed. As Congress and the Administration work to reform our health care system, I hope Secretary Tom Price will accept my invitation to visit the Central Valley and learn more about the communities impacted most by this failed law.

Enjoyed visiting Arvin Public Library yesterday to participate in story time. The California Summer Meal Coalition has partnered with libraries across the state to offer meals and educational resources to students during the summer. Ì†ΩÌ≥ö
Students from Island Elementary School in Lemoore spent their first week of summer in our nation's Capital. I enjoyed showing them the best view of the city from the Speaker's Balcony today.
Today, the President signed the Veterans Affairs Accountability and Whistleblower Protection Act into law. I'll keep fighting to ensure our Central Valley veterans get the care they deserve.
Next month, I'll be hosting a Small Business Workshop in Sanger. Stop by to learn more about growth opportunities, finding capital, and complying with federal regulations!
Thank you to all those who have bravely served to protect our freedom.   Happy Independence Day!

Today, the House will consider my bill (the #GROWAct) to reform the federal laws that have resulted in hundreds of billions of gallons of water being flushed into the ocean.
Did you know, more water flows into the ocean than is directed to the Central Valley for residential and agricultural use?

11-year-old Elijah from Bakersfield stopped by the office today to share with me how type 1 diabetes has impacted his life and how critical research is to finding a cure. This impressive young man has a bright future in front of him!
I joined with Representative Jeff Denham to introduce H.R. 3451, the CARE Act today. Our bill will improve access to physicians in medically underserved areas - like the Central Valley.
While visiting his cousin Forrest, who attends West Point Military Academy, Kaiu and his family stopped by for a tour of the Capitol today!

Last Saturday, the House Agriculture Committee hosted a Farm Bill Listening Session in the Central Valley. There's no doubt California agriculture drives the American economy, and gathering input from Valley farmers and ranchers is absolutely critical to drafting the 2018 Farm Bill.
Today, and everyday, Americans must come together and unite against racism and hatred. Praying for peace in #Charlottesville.

Each year, I have the privilege of nominating students from our community to attend our nation's Military Service Academies - some of the most prestigious educational institutions in the world. If you, or a student you know, is interested in learning more about this opportunity, please attend the Information Night next month.

Last night, the Senate passed my bill, the Social Security Number Fraud Prevention Act to protect Americans from becoming victims of identity theft. Learn more about the bill here: http://bit.ly/hr624

Living in the Central Valley, I have heard many stories and descriptions of Armenia from my neighbors and friends. Having the opportunity to experience the country they love firsthand was an unforgettable experience.

Sending prayers and gratitude to our troops deployed and the families they leave back home today and every day. #DayOfTheDeployed

Enjoyed discussing agriculture trade, immigration, water, and tax policy with Secretary Perdue in Arvin today. I'm excited to have another advocate in Washington who truly understands the obstacles farmers and ranchers deal with every day.
While our immigration system is in dire need of repair, we cannot let protections for Dreamers expire. Congress must come together to reach a legislative solution.

There's nothing better than meeting my newest constituents in Washington!
When eighth graders from Abraham Lincoln Middle School in Selma wrote letters to me - I thought it was time for a visit! Thanks for the great questions!
